noun.description: A person who provides board for payment. Compare "table". Now historical and rare.
A person who pays for board, a boarder. Compare "table". Now historical and rare.
A person who tables a resolution, motion, etc.
Chiefly with capital initial. A member of the Round Table association; = Round Tabler.

origin: Early 16th century (in an earlier sense). Partly from table + -er, and partly from table + -er. In sense 1 probably after classical Latin tabulārius accountant, book-keeper, or similar. In sense 2 after Hellenistic Greek τραπεζίτης money changer (New Testament).
